edit  
Poland now





Recent events

On 9 January, Zygmunt Bauman, a prominent Polish-British sociologist and philosopher who developed the idea of liquid modernity, died at the age of 91.
On 6 January, Polish ski jumpers, Kamil Stoch (pictured, right) and Piotr Żyła (left), won the first and second places, respectively, in the Four Hills Tournament.
During the first week of January, 46 people in Poland died from cold, as the temperatures fell to −20 °C.

Ongoing events

A disagreement between the Constitutional Tribunal on the one side and the legislative and executive powers, fully controlled by the Law and Justice party since 2015, on the other results in a constitutional crisis.

Holidays and observances in February 2017
(statutory public holidays in bold)




Valentine's Day, 14 February
Fat Thursday (Polish doughnuts pictured), 23 February

